e-x-philippines-release-date |archivedate=November 9, 2017 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n}}{{Collapsible list|framestyle=border:none; padding:0; |title=December 7, 2017\n|[[Chile]]\n}}\n{{Collapsible list|framestyle=border:none; padding:0; |title=December 8, 2017\n|[[Brazil]]\n}}\n{{Collapsible list|framestyle=border:none; padding:0; |title=December 15, 2017\n|[[Indonesia]]\n}}\n| discontinued = {{Start date and age|2018|09|12}}\n| unitssold    =\n| unitsshipped =\n| predecessor  = [[iPhone 7|iPhone 7 / iPhone 7 Plus]]\n| successor    = [[iPhone XS|iPhone XS / iPhone XS Max]]\n| variants     = [[iPhone XS|iPhone XS / iPhone XS Max]]\n| related      = [[iPhone 8|iPhone 8 / iPhone 8 Plus]]\n| type         = [[Smartphone]]\n| form         = [[Slate phone|Slate]]\n| size         = H:&nbsp;{{cvt|143.6|mm|in}}<br />W:&nbsp;{{cvt|70.9|mm|in}}<br />D:&nbsp;{{cvt|7.7|mm|in}}\n| weight       = {{cvt|174|g|oz}}\n| os = '''Original:''' [[iOS 11#11.0.1|iOS 11.0.1]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://9to5mac.com/2017/11/03/ios-11-2-beta-iphone-x/|title=PSA: iOS 11.2 beta not yet available for iPhone X, ships with 11.0.1 [U]|date=November 3, 2017|work=9to5Mac|access-date=November 21, 2017|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171107023936/https://9to5mac.com/2017/11/03/ios-11-2-beta-iphone-x/|archive-date=November 7, 2017|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref><br />'''Current:''' [[iOS 13|iOS 13.4.1]], released {{start date|mf=yes|2020|4|7}}\n| soc          = [[Apple A11 Bionic]]\n| cpu          = [[Multi-core processor|Hexa-core]] [[64-bit]] (2x high power Monsoon cores at 2.39GHz + 4x low power Mistral cores at 1.42GHz)\n| memory       = 3&nbsp;GB [[Mobile DDR#LP-DDR4X|LPDDR4X]] [[Random-access memory|RAM]]\n| storage      = 64 or 256&nbsp;[[Gigabyte|GB]]\n| memory_card  = None\n| battery      = {{nowrap|3.81 [[Volt|V]]}} {{nowrap|10.35 W\u00b7h}} (2716&nbsp;mA\u00b7h) [[Lithium-ion battery|Li-ion]]<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.ifixit.com/Teardown/iPhone+X+Teardown/98975 |ti